{\plain \fs24 Hi Folks.\par
}{\plain \fs24 \par
}{\plain \fs24 This map is a major update of the original Styria1840 V3.20 map. It contains additional events to enhance \softline
freight traffic, more action events and fixes of a few minor issues. It has been the general consensus that this \softline
version is a bit easier to play as far as difficulty level is concerned and offers more variety in game play. \par
}{\plain \fs24   \par
}{\plain \fs24 The map in general, deals with the early development of railroads in Styria which was part of the former \softline
Austrian Monarchy. An effort was made to accurately portray the period\'92s historic and turbulent events into this \softline
map\'92s game play however, the city names, provinces and most borders are represented as they are presently.\par
}{\plain \fs24 \par
}{\plain \fs28 \b\fs28 The overall goals and challenges of this map\'92s game play are as follows:}{\plain \fs24 \par
}{\plain \fs24 \par
}{\plain \fs24 a.) Provide the \'93Sudbahn\'94 connection between Wiener Neustadt and Marburg.\par
}{\plain \fs24 b.) Build a minimum amount of rail lines or invest in industry and fulfill a minimum hauling requirement.\par
}{\plain \fs24 c.) Deal with the events surrounding the Revolution of 1848.\par
}{\plain \fs24 d.) Keep the Monarchy and the Public happy.\par
}{\plain \fs24 e.) Provide service to the logging/lumber, iron/metal and coal industries.\par
}{\plain \fs24 f.) Try to connect to all the other Provinces and deliver the required loads.\par
}{\plain \fs24 g.) Have no company debt and have the highest PNW.\par
}{\plain \fs24 \par
}{\plain \fs28 \b\fs28 Brief description of some of the above goals and challenges:}{\plain \fs24 \par
}{\plain \fs24 \par
}{\plain \fs24 a.) Sudbahn connection.\par
}{\plain \fs24 Once your rails reach the Murzzuschlag area a suggestion to build a station in Murzzuschlag will be made (Do \softline
so). You will be unable to proceed up to the Semmering Pass until two things happen. You have to have \softline
$700,000.00 in Company Cash (half of the $1,400,000.00 of extra construction cost) and at the beginning of the \softline
yearly construction season (April), your construction companies and managers tell you that they are ready. You \softline
have to build a station on top of the Semmering Pass (in the Semmering LA area - right click to locate the area) \softline
and suggest you add a water and sanding tower. You will not have to build your own stations in Lower Austria \softline
to reach this goal but can connect to stations build by the Nordbahn. Make sure to complete the Semmering \softline
Bahn part of the Sudbahn first before connecting Wiener Neustadt to Marburg. Try to complete this map goal as \softline
early as possible since other events are based on having this connection made and there will also be bonuses for \softline
a early connection.\par
}{\plain \fs24 \par
}{\plain \fs24 b.) Build a minimum amount of rail lines or invest in industry and provide a minimum hauling requirement.\par
}{\plain \fs24 At the beginning of the scenario you will be asked to comply with the minimum rail requirement however, you \softline
will be given the opportunity to opt out later in the game. The amount of rail built is checked periodically. You \softline
might get away with not having the required amount in some years as long as it is not in a year the amount is \softline
checked. The amount of required rail as indicated on the status page is what is required by the end of the year.  \softline
The year-end status report will indicate what is needed by the end of the following year.\par
}{\plain \fs24 \par
}{\plain \fs24 c.) Deal with the events surrounding the Revolution of 1848.\par
}{\plain \fs24 The first signs of the revolution period will show up in 1846 with a lowering of the economic activities and end \softline
in 1849. Robberies should increase but the increase in breakdowns and crashes is not my doing.\par
}{\plain \fs24 \par
}{\plain \fs24 d.) Keep the Monarchy and the Public happy.\par
}{\plain \fs24 Many events will play a role in lowering or increasing your popularity with the monarchy or public. The results \softline
of a low popularity are twofold. If it gets too low there is, at a minimum, just a monetary penalty and if it \softline
happens too often it will lead to you being replaced. Game over. If you in any one year lower your popularity \softline
by too much your tycoon days can also be over. \par
}{\plain \fs24 e.) Provide service to the logging/lumber, iron/metal and coal industries.\par
}{\plain \fs24 Your destiny and that of the Oststeirische Holzerei AG and the Steirische Kohlenbergbau Gmbh. and the \softline
Steirische Eisen Werke AG. depends on how well you service those industries. Several events will offer \softline
incentives to make the hauling of freight more attractive.\par
}{\plain \fs24 \par
}{\plain \fs24 f.) Connection to all provinces and delivery of required loads.\par
}{\plain \fs24 One will first need to make the Sudbahn connection before receiving access rights to the provinces of Carinthia, \softline
Burgenland, Salzburg and Upper Austria. Train running rights in a province are given once connection from \softline
one of your stations in that province to Graz is made. A newspaper report informs you of this. \par
}{\plain \fs24 One might find the delivery of goods to be a challenge at times since the means of generating it locally might be \softline
limited. To deliver goods from outside the local area like Leoben as an example and delivering it to Upper \softline
Austria will take about four years.  Note that you will not receive the \'93officially connected\'94 status in a province \softline
until you have also delivered the required loads.\par
}{\plain \fs24 \par
}{\plain \fs28 \b\fs28 Brief description of other events:}{\plain \fs24 \par
}{\plain \fs24 \par
}{\plain \fs24 a.) Semmering tourist deliveries.\par
}{\plain \fs24 This event plays a bit different from the previous version. The passengers now have to be actually delivered to \softline
the station on top of the Semmering Pass. During my games I found it easiest to just set the delivery flag to \softline
yellow (Sell only demanded cargo, leave undemanded cargo on the train to be sold later) for the Semmering \softline
Pass destination since that destination is not likely to demand passengers. Therefore a train schedule might be:\par
}{\plain \fs24 Murzzuschlag (green-yellow),\par
}{\plain \fs24 Semmering Pass (yellow),\par
}{\plain \fs24 Gloggnitz (green-yellow),\par
}{\plain \fs24 Semmering Pass (yellow).\par
}{\plain \fs24 \par
}{\plain \fs24 b.) You will be given an opportunity fairly early in the game to opt out of the minimum rail requirement. Even \softline
though this sounds tempting, to pursue this option successfully is a real challenge due to the Industry \softline
Investment requirement. It will very likely necessitate the merger of one or more of the three Industrial \softline
Companies (Oststeirische Holzerei AG., Steirische Kohlenbergbau Gmbh., and Alpine Eisen Werke AG.) since \softline
you will be required to serve those industries anyhow. Just a warning that this opting out might mean \'93out of \softline
the game\'94.\par
}{\plain \fs24 \par
}{\plain \fs24 c.) One might also be tempted to assume the chairmanship of another railroad company. This could result in an \softline
early stop to the game since there are checks requiring you to be the chairman of the Kaiserliche Steirische \softline
Bahn. Therefore, one needs to be careful in making those excursions.\par
}{\plain \fs24 \par
}{\plain \fs24 d.) There are many events offering many choices but one should not assume that all choices offered are good \softline
ones. There are some events that have just \'93bad - bad\'94 choices, others are \'93good - game over\'94 choices and some \softline
lead you down a path you really don\'92t want to go. But many choices are focused toward supporting the maps \softline
main goals however, the effects will not be noticeable until a few years down the road. Most choices however, \softline
require careful analysis to establish if the choice one is about to make is really consistent with the tasks at hand \softline
or the games overall goals. \par
}{\plain \fs24 \par
}{\plain \fs28 \b\fs28 General information:}{\plain \fs24 \par
}{\plain \fs24 \par
}{\plain \fs24 Even though this map is playable for players of all levels of playing experience, it is recommended for \softline
intermediate and experienced players. It is also suggested, for more stimulating game play, to select all eight \softline
computer players and to select the expert level.\par
}{\plain \fs24 \par
}{\plain \fs24 For most of you the names and areas covered on the map will be somewhat alien and as such difficult to 
remember and/or relate to. At times it might be awkward to make decisions, triggered by events, relating to map \softline
locations. Therefore, it is strongly recommended one familiarize oneself first with the overall layout of the map.\par
}{\plain \fs24 \par
}{\plain \fs24 Game play can be a difficult over the first few years. Please, read the dialog boxes and newspaper reports \softline
carefully since they often contain hints and tips of what one should be doing. During game play please check \softline
your \'93Briefings\'94 to update yourself on some of the activities required or available tasks.\par
}{\plain \fs24 \par
}{\plain \fs24 Depending on your style of play a game may last for many hours. Myself, I do a lot of micro-managing and an \softline
average game takes a minimum of four to six hours. But don\'92t let that scare you off. You will hardly notice it.\par
}{\plain \fs24 \par
}{\plain \fs24 It is also suggested you save the game often since your response to many events can have dire consequences. At \softline
the worst it could be the end of the game right there. But as a astute railroad operator and friend of the \softline
Monarchy it most likely will not happen to you.\par
}{\plain \fs24 \par
}{\plain \fs24 The loading of this map takes on my computer (233Mhz AMD K6-2) about 4 minutes. So please be patient. It \softline
most likely will be worth the wait.\par
}{\plain \fs24 \par
}{\plain \fs28 \b\fs28 Restrictions:}{\plain \fs24 \par
}{\plain \fs24 \par
}{\plain \fs24 Restrictions for setting the throttle, starting a new company or multiple companies, are in effect. There are no \softline
customs at borders.\par
